        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "• Compensation and benefits expenses of $8,542 million in the current quarter increased 14% from the prior year quarter, primarily due to an increase in the formulaic payout to Wealth Management advisors and higher discretionary incentive compensation within Institutional Securities, both on higher revenues.",
            "block_bbox": [
                85,
